  "description": "Demolition of existing buildings and redevelopment of the site to provide ground floor commercial space (Class E Shop, Class E restaurant or caf , Class E office, Class E gym, Class E medical) and residential units within a part 3, part 4, and part 5 storey building with associated parking, private and communal space, cycle storage, secure bike store, refuse space and public realm improvements.",
  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed development would, by reason of its substantial scale, height, bulk and proximity to the boundaries of the site,give rise to an intrusive and overbearing form of development, which is out of scale and incompatible with the adjoining rear garden environment, thereby having a materially harmful impact on the amenity of neighbouring residential properties. Further due to the significant number of terraces, balconies and amenity areas to the rear elevation of the proposed development in close proximity to the neighbouring buildings, the proposal would give rise to significant loss of privacy resulting in harm to the amenity of the neighbouring buildings. Therefore, the proposal would result in significant loss of privacy and amenity to the occupiers of neighbouring  residential dwellings, contrary to Policy 7 of the Local Plan 2021. .",
    "The proposal with particular reference to deliveries and refuse collection would be likely to give rise to potential hazards to the safe and free flow of traffic contrary to Policy 23 of the adopted Local Plan.",
    "In the absence of an appropriate energy statement and the inability to secure contributions towards carbon reduction,  the proposal fails to provide a sustainable development, contrary to the provisions of Policies 33 and 36 of the Local Plan and Policy S13 of the London Plan",
    "In the absence of a legal agreement to provide a training and recruitment scheme for the local workforce during the construction period, the proposal would be contrary to the provisions of Policy 22 of the Local Plan.",
    "In the absence of a satisfactorily completed legal agreement the provision of affordable housing and appropriate review mechanisms cannot be secured and therefore the application is contrary to Policy 4 of the Local Plan and policy H4 of London Plan.",
    "In the absence of a legal agreement to secure Highway contributions for to extend the traffic island and a legal agreement to prevent the future occupiers of the site being able to park within the nearby streets,  the proposal would be likely to increase the potential hazards to the safe and free flow of traffic contrary to Policy 23 of the Local Plan.",
    "For Residential Development Only",
    "Please be advised that approval of this application from 1st September 2019 (either by London Borough of Havering, or subsequently by PINS if allowed on appeal following a refusal by London Borough of Havering) the application would be subject to CIL liability.",
    "In this case the proposal is liable for the Mayor of London Community Infrastructure Levy (CIL) and Havering CIL (HCIL). Mayoral CIL is calculated at £25.00 per square metre, subject to indexation. HCIL is charged at an approved rate of be £125/m² of GIA, subject to indexation. The total net residential floor space would be 1990 sqm. This would yield £49,900 mayoral CIL and £249,500 of Havering CIL.",
    "You are advised to visit the planning portal website where you can download the appropriate document templates.",
    "http://www.planningportal.gov.uk/planning/applications/howtoapply/whattosubmit/cil",
    "Statement Required by Article 35 (2) of the Town and Country Planning (Development Management Procedure) (England) Order 2015: In accordance with paragraph 38 of the National Planning Policy Framework, improvements required to make the proposal acceptable were negotiated with the agent of the applicant. However whilst the scheme was amended, these were not sufficient to overcome the objections to the scheme and the applicant declined to make the necessary amendments."
  ],
